uboot.zip is a linux server micro image able to run native from cd and
usb-drive or emulated under windows, linux and macosx.

To create a new iso image unzip uboot.zip then cd into uboot and run
eja.it/make_iso.sh, the image will be created on uboot parent directory.

To create a bootable pendrive unzip uboot.zip into pendrive main directory
then run eja.it/make_usb.sh

To run local unzip the uboot.zip file somewhere into your computer and
run respective:

linux.sh for Linux (any version)
windows.bat for Windows (>=95)
macosx.command for MacOsX (>=10.3)


For any other information please go to http://uboot.sourceforge.net/